Fresh, local eel caught in the Moonpier harbor and grilled in a rich, smokey sauce. Served with a side of locally-grown corn and carrots.
Fresh, local mackerel caught in the Moonpier harbor and sautéed with a variety of vegetables. It is a spicy and filling local favorite.
A delicately sweet bread pudding made from locally grown wheat and almonds imported from Khem. It is a favorite among the local children, especially when topped with a spoonful of iced cream!
This bass has been cooked into a pie with a mixture of hearty vegetables and potatoes. A fishy delicacy!
Carrots: The bane of small children everywhere who won't eat their vegitables. They are nutritious, however; and reputedly eating enough of them will allow one to see better in the dark.

A tender, juicy shark steak presents a unique culinary experience, characterized by its firm yet delicate texture and rich flavor profile. The meat is exceptionally moist, with a succulent quality that combines the oceanic essence of the sea with a slightly sweet undertone. The steak boasts a pinkish-white color and a fine-grained texture, allowing it to soak up the marinade and seasonings accompanying it. Cooked to perfection, this shark steak offers a delectable balance of tenderness and juiciness, making it a distinctive choice for those seeking a flavorful and satisfying seafood dish.
Boiled in a seasoned tomato sauce, these oysters are full of flavor

While not as nutritious as special rye bread, it is certainly more edible than its moldy alternative.
Eating considerable quantities of bread has been known to dilute or even absorb some ingested toxins.

This piping-hot cherry cobbler is fresh from the oven, tantalizing your senses with an irresistible aroma. The air is filled with the sweet perfume of ripe cherries mingling with the comforting notes of golden-brown, buttery crust. As you take your first bite, your taste buds are greeted by the warm embrace of succulent, juicy cherries bursting with tart sweetness. The cobbler's crust cradles a perfect balance of crisp and tender, its buttery layers adding a hint of richness that complements the fruity symphony within. Each spoonful unveils a medley of textures -- the soft, molten cherries harmonizing with the satisfyingly crunchy crust, creating a dessert that dances on your palate. With every bite, the decadent warmth and harmonious blend of flavors make this hot dessert a delightful, comforting indulgence.
Goat's milk imported from The Dale.
Made from fresh, local ingredients as well as fruit imported from The Dale, this blend of juices is mixed and sweetened to just the right taste.
Iced tea, served sweet and cold. Complete with a side of lemon, and sugar cubes if you want them!

Tea is an infusion of hot water and the flowers, leaves, fruit, roots or bark of one or more plants. This one is subtly  sweetened with honey and nutmeg, with just a splash of vanilla. Milk and additional sugar are available to your taste!
Fresh milk, sourced from the two cows in Moonpier. When they're low on stock, they order some from The Dale, though.
Freshly pressed orange juice, from oranges brought in from Khalem.
Fresh water so pure that it sparkles. It is chilled and so refreshing!
